---
title: Microservices Architecture — Telegram Bot
---
graph TB
    TG([Telegram API])

    subgraph docker["Docker Compose"]
        GW[bot-gateway<br/>:3000<br/>long polling · routing · OAuth callback]
        BK[booking-service<br/>:3001<br/>locations · resources · bookings · slots]
        CAL[calendar-service<br/>:3002<br/>OAuth · Google · MS · connections]
        PAY[payment-service<br/>:3003<br/>YooKassa invoices · pre-checkout]
        NOT[notification-service<br/>async only<br/>outbound Telegram messages]
        ANA[analytics-service<br/>:3005<br/>stats · heatmap · reports]
        ADM[admin-service<br/>:3006<br/>proxy to booking + analytics]

        REDIS[(Redis Streams<br/>event bus)]
        PG[(PostgreSQL<br/>4 schemas)]
    end

    TG <-->|long polling| GW
    GW -->|HTTP sync| BK
    GW -->|HTTP sync| CAL
    GW -->|HTTP sync| PAY
    GW -->|HTTP sync| ADM

    PAY -->|publish payment.completed| REDIS
    BK  -->|publish booking.created| REDIS
    BK  -->|publish booking.cancelled| REDIS
    PAY -->|publish notification.send| REDIS
    ANA -->|publish report.ready| REDIS

    REDIS -->|consume| NOT
    REDIS -->|consume| ANA

    NOT -->|sendMessage · sendInvoice| TG

    BK  --- PG
    CAL --- PG
    PAY --- PG
    ANA --- PG
